@chrsmith Pulumi installs plugins to ~/.pulumi. This installation doesn't respect $HOME environment variable, it uses `getent`, which gets the home from `/etc/passwd`.

So when I run `npm install` (this could also be a pulumi login or pulumi preview command) manually, some post-install script fetches the required plugins; Pulumi won't run `npm install`, hence fetching the plugins, when `node_modules` exists.

So by the time I reach `pulumi up`, `node_modules` exists and the plugins do not; as that directory isn't persisted by GitHub Actions across jobs.

Noting for posterity the spec at https://tools.ietf.org/id/draft-jones-json-web-token-04.html#rfc.appendix.Appendix%20B aligns with this code

(Specifically)
```
If the length mod 4 is 0, no padding is added;
if the length mod 4 is 2, two '=' padding characters are added;
if the length mod 4 is 3, one '=' padding character is added;
if the length mod 4 is 1, the input is malformed.
```

