This JSON tag won't work. It doesn't support descending into children like this.
You need a nested struct for the `Parent`, and a corresponding `URN`.

https://go.dev/play/p/t53DwbnG-2j

e.g.

```go
type ResourceResult struct {
  // ...
  Parent struct { URN string `json:"urn"` } `json:"parent"`
}
```

Or you can declare a `type StructURN string` that implements [json.Unmarshaler](https://pkg.go.dev/encoding/json#Unmarshaler) to extract the URN from a struct field.
Maybe something like this:

```go
type ParentURN string

func (p *ParentURN) UnmarshalJSON(bs []byte) error {
  var inner struct{ URN string `json:"urn"` }
  err := json.Unmarshal(bs, &inner)
  if err != nil { return err }
  *p = inner.URN
  return nil
}
```

