You need to release `pCoreRef` before returning. More in general, I suggest to centralize the cleanup logic in one place, and use a goto.
This construct is used pretty much everywhere in psutil, so you can search for "error:" in the C files to know what I mean, but long story short what I'm suggesting is something like this (not tested).
Every time there is an error, anywhere, just set exception and then do `goto error;`.

```c
PyObject *
psutil_cpu_freq(PyObject *self, PyObject *args) {
    CFTypeRef pCoreRef = NULL;
    CFTypeRef eCoreRef = NULL;
    io_iterator_t iter = NULL;
    io_registry_entry_t entry = NULL;

    ...

    eCoreRef = IORegistryEntryCreateCFProperty(entry, CFSTR("voltage-states1-sram"), kCFAllocatorDefault, 0);
    if (!eCoreRef) {
        PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError, "'voltage-states1-sram' property not found");
        goto error;
    }

    ...

    error:
        if (pCoreRef != NULL):
            CFRelease(pCoreRef);
        if (eCoreRef != NULL):
            CFRelease(eCoreRef);
        if (iter != NULL)
            IOObjectRelease(iter);
        if (entry != NULL)
            IOObjectRelease(entry);
        return NULL;
}
```

